         <abstract>
            <p>For the Lie algebras L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(H(2)) and L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(W(2)), we study their infinitesimal deformations and the corresponding global ones. We show that, as in the case of L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(W(1)), each integrable infinitesimal deformation of L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(H(2)) and L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(W(2)) can be represented by a 2-cocycle that defines a global deformation by means of a trivial extension. We also illustrate that all deformations of L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(H(2)) arise as restrictions of deformations of L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;(W(2)).</p>
          </abstract>
